<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='274000' id='t-274000'>So the hyperbole is not actually surprising.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 4:48
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='277000' id='t-277000'>And what is the great king, the powerful king,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='279000' id='t-279000'>the king of the four quarters of the world going to do?</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='282000' id='t-282000'>He goes on to say that, having conquered Babylon,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='285000' id='t-285000'>he will at once let all the peoples</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='288000' id='t-288000'>that the Babylonians -- Nebuchadnezzar and Belshazzar --</span>
