<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='376000' id='t-376000'>The central element, still,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='379000' id='t-379000'>of the notion of return,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='381000' id='t-381000'>a central part</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='383000' id='t-383000'>of the life of Judaism.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='385000' id='t-385000'>As you all know, that return from exile,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='387000' id='t-387000'>the second temple,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='389000' id='t-389000'>reshaped Judaism.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='391000' id='t-391000'>And that change,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='393000' id='t-393000'>that great historic moment,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='395000' id='t-395000'>was made possible by Cyrus, the king of Persia,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='399000' id='t-399000'>reported for us in Hebrew in scripture</span>
