<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='504000' id='t-504000'>The Greek historian Xenophon</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='507000' id='t-507000'>wrote his book &quot;Cyropaedia&quot;</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='509000' id='t-509000'>promoting Cyrus as the great ruler.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='511000' id='t-511000'>And throughout European culture afterward,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='514000' id='t-514000'>Cyrus remained the model.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='517000' id='t-517000'>This is a 16th century image</span>
