<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='575000' id='t-575000'>in the middle of the 19th century:</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='577000' id='t-577000'>Are the scriptures reliable? Can we trust them?</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='580000' id='t-580000'>We only knew</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='582000' id='t-582000'>about the return of the Jews and the decree of Cyrus</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='584000' id='t-584000'>from the Hebrew scriptures.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='586000' id='t-586000'>No other evidence.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='588000' id='t-588000'>Suddenly, this appeared.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='590000' id='t-590000'>And great excitement</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='592000' id='t-592000'>to a world where those who believed in the scriptures</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='594000' id='t-594000'>had had their faith in creation shaken</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='596000' id='t-596000'>by evolution, by geology,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='598000' id='t-598000'>here was evidence</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='600000' id='t-600000'>that the scriptures were historically true.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='602000' id='t-602000'>It's a great 19th century moment.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
10:16
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='605000' id='t-605000'>But -- and this, of course, is where it becomes complicated --</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='610000' id='t-610000'>the facts were true,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='612000' id='t-612000'>hurrah for archeology,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='615000' id='t-615000'>but the interpretation was rather more complicated.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='618000' id='t-618000'>Because the cylinder account and the Hebrew Bible account</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='621000' id='t-621000'>differ in one key respect.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='623000' id='t-623000'>The Babylonian cylinder</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='625000' id='t-625000'>is written by the priests</span>
